node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by INSANE LUXURY on July 31, 2021 tagging @platinumtimesco. May be an image of wrist watch.

node.text:
@platinumtimesco with their mexican Richard Mille timepieces, the RM 011 Flyback Chronograph on the right and the RM 030 Automatic on the left, both made in DLC Titanium with the country’s national colors. These limited edition’s RMs feature green inner bezel, white indicators and black/red crown. The chronograph has the red numeral “10” representing the number of pieces made in this exclusive edition. #RichardMille

Photo: @platinumtimesco

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by INSANE LUXURY in Tokyo, Japan with @rolex, and @alexzverev123. May be an image of 1 person and wrist watch.

node.text:
@alexzverev123 of Germany defeated the ATP No. 1 @djokernole to reach the final of the Olympic Games tennis tournament. In this shot after the match he was wearing a @rolex Sky-Dweller in stainless steel with blue dial with jubilee bracelet. The Sky-Dweller has been introduced at BaselWorld 2012 and is still one of Rolex' most complicated watches to date, it features an annual calendar and a second time zone function. Zverev is the first Rolex ambassador that previously partnered with Richard Mille for the creation of his own RM 67-02 ‘Alex Zverev’ made with Germany’s flag colors. #Rolex

Retail price: $16,550.00
Market price: $30,000.00

Photo: @teamdeutschland | @rolex

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by INSANE LUXURY in Madrid, Spain with @raphaelvarane, and @patekphilippe. May be an image of 1 person and wrist watch.
Photo by INSANE LUXURY in Brunei with @patekphilippe. May be an image of 4 people and wrist watch.

node.text:
The Sultan of Brunei Hassanal Bolkiah
wears the new @patekphilippe Nautilus 5711/1A-014 in stainless steel with green dial. The special sunburst olive-green dial is horizontally embossed and features gold applied hour markers with luminescent coating. This timepiece has been introduced to celebrate this iconic reference on its last year of production, for the first time with green dial. #PatekPhilippe

Retail price: $34,893.00
Market price: $350,000.00

Photo: @experimental_angle | @patekphilippe

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by INSANE LUXURY on July 29, 2021 tagging @thuggerthugger1, and @richardmille. May be an image of 1 person and wrist watch.

node.text:
The American rapper Young Thug in his latest appearance was wearing a @richardmille RM 16-01 Automatic ‘Réglisse’, part of the brand’s BonBon collection unveiled in 2019. The case of this sweet timepiece is made in blush pink and yellow TZP ceramic while the caseband is made of white gold. The liquorice dial is in grade 5 titanium and black chrome treated. Young Thug is not the first rapper to wear a Richard Mille BonBon, @meekmill owns the RM 16-01 ‘Citron’ and @travisscott a RM 07-03 ‘Marshmallow’. #RichardMille

Retail price: $ 138,000.00
Market price: $ 300,000.00

Photo: @connor.films | @richardmille

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by INSANE LUXURY in Milwaukee, Wisconsin with @giannis_an34, and @rolex. May be an image of one or more people and people standing.

node.text:
An iconic shot of NBA star Giannis Antetokounmpo holding his MVP award with a @rolex Sky-Dweller on wrist. The player that led Milwaukee Bucks to win the NBA finals during this season has shown love for watches, seen wearing over than ten different Rolex. During the Victory Parade hew was wearing a Sky-Dweller in stainless steel with black dial, a watch that reminds the one of Micheal Jordan (blue dial). #Rolex

Photo: @gettyimages

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by INSANE LUXURY on July 29, 2021 tagging @fabiocannavaroofficial, and @purnell_official. May be an image of 1 person, wrist watch and text that says 'FC PURNELL 기'.

node.text:
The 2006 FIFA World Cup and Ballon d'Or winner @fabiocannavaroofficial wears a @purnell_official Escape II in black carbon with green details, powered by the fastest tourbillon on earth. It features two eye-catching green outer cages of the double triple-axis tourbillon, black ruthenium dial with hand-polished hands, finished with hand-applied green lacquer indexes displaying hours, minutes and power reserve. #Purnell

Limited edition: 3 pieces
Retail price: $450,000.00

Photo: @fabiocannavaroofficial | @purnell_official

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by INSANE LUXURY on July 28, 2021 tagging @timatiofficial, and @jacobandco. May be an image of ring and wrist watch.

node.text:
@timatiofficial wears a piece-unique @jacobandco Billionaire III in white gold, fully covered by emerald-cut diamonds. The case is impressively set with 76 emerald-cut diamonds, inner ring set with emerald-cut 76 diamonds, bridges set with 57 baguette-cut diamonds and crown set with one rose-cut diamonds. The insane bracelet is set with 504 emerald-cut diamonds. This watch has been inspired by the one and only Billionaire with its approximate carat weight of 260 carats (price-tag of $18 million) owned by @floydmayweather. #JacobandCo

Limited edition: 1 piece
Retail price: $ 3,000,000.00

Photo: @jacobandco

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by INSANE LUXURY in Los Angeles, California with @richardmille. May be an image of wrist watch and text.

node.text:
Jay-Z jumping out his private jet wearing the first ever @richardmille Tourbillon made in partnership with @rafaelnadal back in 2010. The RM 027 weighs less than 20 g (including the strap), one of the lightest watches ever produced. This watch revolutionized the world of watchmaking as the first tourbillon watch to be worn on court capable of withstanding the shocks incurred for hours during a tennis match. The tennis legend Nadal has won several trophies with this watch on wrist, including his second Wimbledon in 2010. #RichardMille

Retail price: $ 525,000.00

Photo: @richardmille

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by INSANE LUXURY in Miami, Florida with @maluma, and @rolex. May be an image of 1 person and wrist watch.

node.text:
@maluma wears a new 41mm @rolex Oyster Perpetual ref. 124300 in stainless steel with turquoise ‘Tiffany’ blue dial. Introduced in 2020 the new Oyster Perpetual has been unveiled with a dynamic and vibrant new look, offering lacquer dials in five new colours: candy pink, turquoise blue, yellow, coral red and Rolex green. #Rolex 

Retail price : $5,900.00
Market price : $19,500.00

Photo : @maluma | @rolex
